olive oil
1 packet beef strips
1 packet garlic paste
1 packet Honey-Soy Sauce
1 packet Microwavable Basmati Rice
1 packet Crushed Peanuts
1 cucumber
1 packet Yuzu Vinaigrette
1 packet garlic aioli
1 packet Crispy Shallots
1 bag herbs
1 bag Asian Slaw Mix

• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over high heat
• Cook beef strips in batches until browned, 1 min
• Return beef to pan, add garlic paste and honey-soy sauce and cook until slightly reduced and fragrant, 1 min
• Set aside.

• Microwave rice until steaming, 2-3 mins
• Add peanuts to the rice packet. Season and stir.

• Chop cucumber
• In a bowl, combine cucumber, slaw mix and yuzu vinaigrette. Season
• Plate up peanut rice, slaw and beef
• Serve with garlic aioli and shallots. Garnish with torn herbs